    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">fellowship<br />
the key to the deck is shoulder to shoulder and the white arrows of lorien.  the opponent is in a no-win situation when they enter their shadow phase.  if they play minions  you use the white arrows to discard the rest of their hand.  if they dont play minions you walk for free.  <br />
<br />
dont exert galadriel to play elves for free unless you know you cant use the mirror on a given turn.  in fact i dont think i exerted her to play an elf for free the entire tournament.  <br />
<br />
<br />
shadow<br />
the only problem this deck has is direct wounds such as archery, paths, and arv.  for the most part you do all the damage from 4-6.  usually at 4 legolas will double exert to kill a rager.  after that the opponent is in trouble.  a rager with a sword and a savagery does 4 wounds and the opponent overturns 6 cards.  <br />
<br />
<br />
in most cases, especially against smaller decks and/or moria the opponent will be out of cards by site 6 or 7.  the facilitates an easy walk from 6-9 for you.  what people dont realize is that while this deck kills the opponent&#39;s shadow side is that it is also brutal on their fellowship.  its extremely difficult to stay alive against the uruks when you are having half your deck discarded or overturned.  in fact i won probably half my games by overwhelming. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
